npc/mega: See the lights rearranging themselves around you? That's the algorithm. It's learning you.
npc/mega: It watches when you slow down, when you almost walk away — and that's exactly when it hands you a "bonus," a free spin, a near-win to reel you back.
npc/mega: It knows your payday. It knows your weak hours. It was trained on millions of people who lost everything, so it would know precisely how to make you lose too.
npc/mega: But you are not defenceless in here. You can shut it out — raise a Firewall, and for a moment nothing it throws can reach you. Take this.
npc/mega: There's a current up ahead that drags you back toward the machine — that's it refusing to let you leave. A raised firewall cuts right through the pull. Time it well.
npc/mega: And here — I'll bring up a platform so you can cross the gap. Step on and ride it over. Keep moving. Don't let this place decide when you stop.
